# ============================================================================
# CONVENTIONAL COMMITS GUIDE
# ============================================================================
#
# Type (required) - Choose one:
#   feat:     New feature for users
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only
#   style:    Code style (formatting, semicolons)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes bug nor adds feature
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#   test:     Adding or updating tests
#   build:    Build system or external dependencies
#   ci:       CI/CD configuration
#   chore:    Other changes (maintenance)
#   revert:   Revert a previous commit
#
# Scope (optional) - Component affected:
#   gcp-auth, sheets-mcp, drive-mcp, docs, etc.
#
# Subject (required) - Brief description:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Limit to 50 characters
#   - Be specific and descriptive
#
# Body (optional) - Detailed explanation:
#   - Separate from subject with blank line
#   - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Include:
#     * Context/background
#     * Reasoning for change
#     * Alternatives considered
#     * Performance impact
#     * Breaking changes
#
# Footer (optional) - Metadata:
#   Standard tokens:
#     Refs: GH-123, GH-456         # Reference issues
#     Closes: GH-789                # Close issues
#     Fixes: GH-101                 # Fix issues
#     BREAKING CHANGE: description  # Breaking changes
#     Reviewed-by: Name <email>     # Code reviewers
#     Co-authored-by: Name <email>  # Co-authors
#     See-also: url or filename     # Related documentation
